Results._refObjectName: REGRESSION ISSUE : Job of type "Remove Design from Construction View" is running continuously.
Results.Description:
1 Create a new design and transition it to Design Layout.
2 Make a temporary text change (View > Text Move) to a pole annotation.
3 Create a new pole with a CU
4 Create a free text annotation (Edit > Annotation...)
5 Create an annotation formula by placing the first trail point (of 3pt trail)
  on a primary conductor _then actavated annotation editor (Edit > Annotation...),
  selected Appendable field Phase and pressed Insert to insert the formula.

6 Navigated the design to As-built and Integrated the design, Verified that "Merge and Post Design" job is completed. Observed that "Remove Design from Construction View" job is running continuously, which never completes. Also observed that Construction View is displayed as writable

Analysis :

When a temporary text change (View > Text Move) to a pole annotation is made in the design. Inserted a Pole by adding a CO to it. Post the design, Observed that "Remove Design from Construction View" job is running continuously.

For regular cases like modifying objects and Integrating the design to DT. This is not failing.
Results.Name: REGRESSION ISSUE : Job of type "Remove Design from Construction View" is running continuously.

Results._refObjectName: Internal name is displayed for Job Region instead of 'Send Joins to Explorer' and clicking on this doesn't export anything to explorer window-djb
Results.Description:
Steps to Reproduce :

1) Invoke EO_DM Application.

2) Select a 'Job Region' from the map view.

3) The selected Job region gets populated in the editor.

4) Goto 'Specials' in the editor toolbar.

Issues :

  • If you try to expand it, we can see that the Internal name is getting displayed.(Please see the Snapshot attached). Internal name shouldn't be displayed.
  • When we click the Internal name(which should be 'Send Joins to Explorer'), nothing is exported to explorer.

Results._refObjectName: REGRESSION ISSUE : TBK Error is received while accessing DLT's
Results.Description:
Acceptance Criteria

  • Able to Activate an rwo inserting  DLT that is configured to popup an MOE and place the rwo successfully. 
  • CRD129114 needs to be tested as part of this defect.

Technical Analysis -- Taj

This is caused by a missing a core method. A Core Bug CBG00132072 was raised. Core teams response was that as this method is restricted, it's removal is justified and DEsign Manager has to deal with this.

Looks like we are not going to get any help from core.

In my openion the approach shuld be

        1. Investihgate how core is coping with the missing method i.e what is the code in core that has   replaced next_available_editor() calls in core

2. Investigare 111997_2a, 2b.....  series of patches

 End Of Technical Analysis

Steps

  1. Create a new project/design or activate an existing writable design
  2. Choose any DLT which will bring you MOE. E.g. Generic Gas Main
  3. Attempt to place it on the map, Below Traceback error is recevied.
